      • getDistributedAmountForUnexecutedDist

        MonetaryAmount getDistributedAmountForUnexecutedDist()
        Return the net amount to apply to invoice items, excluding suspense items which are counted separately. Unlike BaseDistStubI.getNetDistributedToInvoiceItems(), which only counts the amount distributed on executed items, this method counts the distributed amount across all (non-reversed) dist items whether executed or not. This can be useful when attempting to get information about a saved dist, or a dist that you are currently in the process of creating/distributing.
        Returns:
        The total of all net amounts distributed to invoice items

      • getSuspenseAmountForUnexecutedDist

        MonetaryAmount getSuspenseAmountForUnexecutedDist()
        Return the net suspense amount in this distribution. Unlike BaseDistStubI.getNetInSuspense() , which only counts the suspense amount on executed items, this method counts the suspense amount across all (non-reversed) dist items whether executed or not. This can be useful when attempting to get information about a saved dist, or a dist that you are currently in the process of creating/distributing.
        Returns:
        The total of all net amounts in suspense

      • getNetDistributedAmountForSavedOrExecuted

        MonetaryAmount getNetDistributedAmountForSavedOrExecuted()
        If the BaseDist has been executed, returns BaseDistStubI.getNetDistributedToInvoiceItems(). Otherwise returns getDistributedAmountForUnexecutedDist() which counts across BaseDistItem dist items, excluding BaseSuspDistItem suspense items, whether executed or not.
        Returns:
        The total of all net amounts distributed to invoice items

      • getNetSuspenseAmountForSavedOrExecuted

        MonetaryAmount getNetSuspenseAmountForSavedOrExecuted()
        If the BaseDist has been executed, returns the value of BaseDistStubI.getNetInSuspense()t. Otherwise returns getSuspenseAmountForUnexecutedDist() which counts across all BaseSuspDistItem suspense items whether executed or not.
        Returns:
        The total of all net amounts in suspense in this distribution

      • redistributeWithAmounts

        BaseDist redistributeWithAmounts(@Nonnull
                               java.util.Map<ProducerCode,java.util.Map<Charge,AllocationPool>> amounts)
        This method with attempt to redistribute this payment's undistributed funds to any invoice items on the charges passed in, but the amount to distribute to each charge will be limited to the amount under that charge's map entry.

        The producer code should be null if this is a direct bill payment or an angecy cycle promise as those kinds of dist items do not target producer codes. However, agency payment items target their commission amount to apply to the primary item commission that matches their producer code. So when redistributing agency payment amounts, we must track how much commission to reapply to given producer codes on charges as well as tracking the gross to reapply to the charges.

        Parameters:
        amounts - the map of amounts that should be reapplied, broken down by the charges and possibly the producer codes that these amounts should target
        Returns:
        the redistributed DirectBillPayment (may not be be the same instance)
